A survey in Shanghai has revealed that one in eight people in the city suffer from overweight.
The study shows that the 12 percent obesity is to the standard in developed countries.
The survey was carried out among 14,000 people895 adults and over 9,093 young people from nine districts in the city.
It was conducted by Shanghai Medical Sciences University and Shanghai Xiangshan Traditional Chinese Medicine Hospital.
The survey indicated that differences in age and education levels can influence the ratio of obesity.
